race.comment: The maidens kick us off. LADY MILAN (10) was well-found on debut but just went down by the narrowest of margins around this circuit. Will have derived a stack of benefit from that race day experience and where there's smoke there's fire. Can go one better against this line-up. Former Victorian BARRELLING (16) is having his first run for the Gollan yard but looked handy winning a recent trial and should find this easier than what he faced down south. Respect any market moves. EXTREME TASTE (14) gets some weight off with the claim and is a definite top-three contender based on that debut effort. RATENOTICE (13) is another former Mexican who should be kept very safe first run for the new yard.
